Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getUsefulSkewMode(25.10)                              getUsefulSkewMode(25.10)

Name
       getUsefulSkewMode  -  Returns the current setting of the setUsefulSkew-
       Mode command

Syntax
       getUsefulSkewMode

       [-help]

       [-nonDefault]

       [-opt_skew_apply_delay_limits_to_full_flow]

       [-opt_skew_delay_pre_cts]

       [-opt_skew_macro_only]

       [-opt_skew_max_allowed_delay]

       [-opt_skew_min_allowed_delay]

       [-opt_skew_no_boundary]

       [-quiet]

       Returns the current setting of the setUsefulSkewMode command.  The  se-
       tUsefulSkewMode  command  is  used  to  set global paramaters for clock
       skewing during optimization.

       If you do not specify a parameter, the software returns information for
       all of the setUseFulSkewMode mode parameters.

Parameters
       <parameter_names>
              Returns information for the specified parameter. You can specify
              one or more parameters.

              See setUsefulSkewMode for parameter descriptions.

       -nonDefault
              Returns the current settings of the setUsefulSkewMode parameters
              that are not default.

       -quiet Returns the current settings for the specified parameters in Tcl
              list format only.

              If you specify -quiet without any parameters, the  software  re-
              turns  the  current settings of all setUsefulSkewMode parameters
              in Tcl list format.

Examples
              * The following command returns the current setting of  the  se-
                tUsefulSkewMode -opt_skew_delay_pre_cts parameter:

                getUsefulSkewMode -opt_skew_delay_pre_cts

                The software returns the following information:

                -opt_skew_delay_pre_cts true # bool, default=true

                true

              * The following command returns the current settings for all the
                setUsefulSkewMode parameters:

                getUsefulSkewMode

                The software returns the following information:

                -opt_skew_apply_delay_limits_to_full_flow  false  #  bool, de-
                fault=false

                -opt_skew_delay_pre_cts true                     #  bool,  de-
                fault=true

                -opt_skew_macro_only  false                       #  bool, de-
                fault=false

                -opt_skew_max_allowed_delay 1                   #  float,  de-
                fault=1, min=0, max=1000

                -opt_skew_min_allowed_delay  0                    # float, de-
                fault=0, min=0, max=1000

                -opt_skew_no_boundary false                      #  bool,  de-
                fault=false

                {opt_skew_apply_delay_limits_to_full_flow false} {opt_skew_de-
                lay_pre_cts       true}       {opt_skew_macro_only      false}
                {opt_skew_max_allowed_delay 1} {opt_skew_min_allowed_delay  0}
                {opt_skew_no_boundary false}

              * The  following  command returns the current setting of the se-
                tUsefulSkewMode -opt_skew_delay_pre_cts parameter in Tcl  list
                format only:

                getUsefulSkewMode -opt_skew_delay_pre_cts -quiet

                The software returns the following information:

                true

              * The following command returns the current settings for all se-
                tUsefulSkewMode parameters in Tcl list format only:

                getUsefulSkewMode -quiet

                The software returns the following information:

                {opt_skew_apply_delay_limits_to_full_flow false} {opt_skew_de-
                lay_pre_cts       true}       {opt_skew_macro_only      false}
                {opt_skew_max_allowed_delay 1} {opt_skew_min_allowed_delay  0}
                {opt_skew_no_boundary false}

              *

                The following command returns the current non-default settings
                of the setUsefulSkewMode command:

                getUsefulSkewMode -nonDefault

                -opt_skew_macro_only  true              # bool, default=false,
                user setting

                {opt_skew_macro_only true}

